Alembic Database Migrations for AI Community Companions
=======================================================

This directory contains database migration scripts managed by Alembic.

Directory Structure
-------------------
- env.py       : Environment configuration for running migrations
- script.py.mako : Template for generating new migration files
- versions/    : Directory containing migration scripts

Common Commands
---------------

1. Create a new migration (auto-generate from model changes):
   alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description of changes"

2. Create an empty migration (for manual edits):
   alembic revision -m "description of changes"

3. Apply all pending migrations:
   alembic upgrade head

4. Rollback one migration:
   alembic downgrade -1

5. Rollback to a specific revision:
   alembic downgrade <revision_id>

6. Show current revision:
   alembic current

7. Show migration history:
   alembic history

8. Generate SQL without applying (offline mode):
   alembic upgrade head --sql

Environment Variables
---------------------
The database URL is read from the AIC_DATABASE_URL environment variable.
Make sure your .env file is properly configured before running migrations.

Notes
-----
- Always review auto-generated migrations before applying
- Test migrations on a development database first
- Back up production database before applying migrations
- Migration files should never be deleted once applied to production
